   "source": [
    "# Linear Bivariate BMM with SAMBA toy models : switchcos mixing - bilby constrained priors\n",
    "\n",
    "The best way to learn Taweret is to use it. You can run, modify and experiment with this notebook on [GitHub Codespaces](https://github.com/bandframework/Taweret)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "economic-dublin",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This notebook shows how to use the Bayesian model mixing package **Taweret** for a toy problem. \n",
    "\n",
    "Author : Dan Liyanage \n",
    "\n",
    "Date : 11/10/2022\n",
    "\n",
    "More about SAMBA toy models can be found in [Uncertainties here, there, and everywhere: interpolating between small- and large-g expansions using Bayesian Model Mixing](https://arxiv.org/abs/2206.04116)\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "favorite-fancy",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Steps for Bayesian Model Mixing with Taweret**\n",
    "\n",
    "    1. Define your models using BayesModel class in `Taweret.core.bayesmodel` (Only if you want to bring in your own models)\n",
    "    2. Choose a Mixing method (Avilable mixing methods can be found in Taweret/mix)\n",
    "    3. Find the posterior for the mixture weights (parameters in the mixture function) and/or model parameters by training the mixed model. \n",
    "    4. Make predictions! "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "after-peace",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# You will have to change the following imports depending on where you have \n",
    "# the packages installed\n",
    "\n",
    "cwd = os.getcwd()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the first part of this path and append to the sys.path\n",
    "tw_path = cwd.split(\"Taweret/\")[0] + \"Taweret\"\n",
    "sys.path.append(tw_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# For plotting\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "sns.set_context('poster')\n",
    "# To define priors. (uncoment if not using default priors)\n",
    "import bilby\n",
    "\n",
    "# For other operations\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c33c9f9f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Get toy models and the pseudo-experimental data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "loaded-machinery",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Toy models from SAMBA\n",
    "from Taweret.models import samba_models as toy_models\n",
    "\n",
    "m1 = toy_models.Loworder(2, 'uninformative')\n",
    "m2 = toy_models.Highorder(2, 'uninformative')\n",
    "truth = toy_models.TrueModel()\n",
    "exp = toy_models.Data()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "lasting-spokesman",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "g = np.linspace(0.1, 0.6, 10)\n",
    "plot_g = np.linspace(0.01,1,100)\n",
    "m1_prediction = m1.evaluate(plot_g)\n",
    "m2_prediction = m2.evaluate(plot_g)\n",
    "true_output = truth.evaluate(plot_g)\n",
    "exp_data= exp.evaluate(g,error = 0.01)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "dimensional-greene",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7f9022191dd0>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "fig, ax_f = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))\n",
    "ax_f.plot(plot_g, m1_prediction[0].flatten(), label='low order')\n",
    "ax_f.plot(plot_g, m2_prediction[0].flatten(), label='high order')\n",
    "ax_f.plot(plot_g, true_output[0], label='truth')\n",
    "ax_f.scatter(g,exp_data[0], marker='x', label='experimental data')\n",
    "ax_f.set_ylim(1.2,3.2)\n",
    "ax_f.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "limited-application",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##  2. Choose a Mixing method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "thorough-exercise",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "switchcos mixing function has 3                   free parameter(s)\n",
      "Warning : Default prior is set to {'switchcos_0': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='switchcos_0', latex_label='switchcos_0', unit=None, boundary=None), 'switchcos_1': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='switchcos_1', latex_label='switchcos_1', unit=None, boundary=None), 'switchcos_2': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='switchcos_2', latex_label='switchcos_2', unit=None, boundary=None)}\n",
      "To change the prior use `set_prior` method\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Mixing method\n",
    "from Taweret.mix.bivariate_linear import BivariateLinear as BL\n",
    "\n",
    "models= {'low_order':m1,'high_order':m2}\n",
    "mix_model = BL(models_dic=models, method='switchcos') "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f32d8cc2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#####  Need to speceify a constained prior for switchcos. g1 < g3 < g2\n",
    "We follow Bilby documentation on how to specefy a prior with constraints\n",
    "https://lscsoft.docs.ligo.org/bilby/prior.html#prior-constraints"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "18aae651",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'switchcos_0': TruncatedNormal(mu=0.1, sigma=0.05, minimum=0.01, maximum=0.3, name=None, latex_label=None, unit=None, boundary=None),\n",
       " 'switchcos_1': TruncatedNormal(mu=0.6, sigma=0.05, minimum=0, maximum=0.8, name=None, latex_label=None, unit=None, boundary=None),\n",
       " 'switchcos_2': TruncatedNormal(mu=0.4, sigma=0.05, minimum=0, maximum=0.55, name=None, latex_label=None, unit=None, boundary=None),\n",
       " 'z_0': Constraint(minimum=0, maximum=1, name=None, latex_label=None, unit=None),\n",
       " 'z_1': Constraint(minimum=0, maximum=1, name=None, latex_label=None, unit=None)}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#uncoment to change the prior from the default\n",
    "def convert_x_y_to_z(parameters):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Function to convert between sampled parameters and constraint parameter.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    parameters: dict\n",
    "        Dictionary containing sampled parameter values, 'theta_0', 'theta_1', 'theta_2'.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    dict: Dictionary with constraint parameter 'z_0, z_1' added.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    converted_parameters = parameters.copy()\n",
    "    converted_parameters['z_0'] = parameters['switchcos_2'] - parameters['switchcos_0']\n",
    "    converted_parameters['z_1'] = parameters['switchcos_1'] - parameters['switchcos_2']\n",
    "    return converted_parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "from bilby.core.prior import PriorDict, Uniform, Constraint, TruncatedNormal\n",
    "\n",
    "priors = PriorDict(conversion_function=convert_x_y_to_z)\n",
    "# priors['theta_0'] = Uniform(minimum=0.0, maximum=0.3)\n",
    "# priors['theta_1'] = Uniform(minimum=0.0, maximum=0.55)\n",
    "# priors['theta_2'] = Uniform(minimum=0.0, maximum=0.8)\n",
    "\n",
    "priors['switchcos_0'] = TruncatedNormal(0.1, 0.05, 0.01, 0.3)\n",
    "priors['switchcos_1'] = TruncatedNormal(0.6, 0.05, 0, 0.8)\n",
    "priors['switchcos_2'] = TruncatedNormal(0.4, 0.05, 0, 0.55)\n",
    "priors['z_0'] = Constraint(minimum=0, maximum=1)\n",
    "priors['z_1'] = Constraint(minimum=0, maximum=1)\n",
    "mix_model.set_prior(priors)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bf7b6cc1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
